-- Greek creditors say talks to continue Thursday
-- 
-- Thu Jan 19, 2012 7:58am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/01/19/us-greece-iif-idUSTRE80H1XD20120119

 

 ATHENS  (Reuters) - Greece's private creditors said talks on a bond swap scheme would continue on Thursday after a lengthy meeting with senior officials on Wednesday. 
 The International Institute of Finance, which represents private holders of Greek bonds, did not comment in its statement on whether there had been any progress during the latest round of talks. (Reporting by George Georgiopoulos)